A mysterious phenomenon - the swing-by anomaly - has been causing confusion among scientists for years.
Swing-by is a flight manoeuvre by spacecraft in which they gain additional momentum in the gravitational field of a celestial body, such as Earth.
As a result, the probes can save a lot of fuel.
The European-American research probe Cassini-Huygens used this physical trick, as did the solar probe Ulysses.
