In fact, there are irregularities in speed.
The probes become unexpectedly faster or slower.
Until now, physicists have not been able to explain this effect.
They christened it swing-by-anomaly.
Some experts fear that even Albert Einstein's general theory of relativity, which describes the attraction of matter by the curvature of space, may not be entirely correct.
