I do not mean those who wake up and tell us something that happened the day before, but the children who speak while they are asleep.
When it happens to you for the first time, at best you will be terrified, but in reality it does not matter.
This is a positive sleep disorder called speaking in sleep.
It is quite common, especially among children and young people.
Certainly, more than one of you was told that you spoke at night.
This phenomenon can occur occasionally (once in a lifetime, for example, during high fever), or regularly (every day, once a week, once a month), the next day the child cannot remember anything.
There is no single cause that causes this phenomenon.
Often connections are sought with other phenomena in sleep, such as nightmares, panic anxiety at night, enuresis noctura (bedwetting at night), speaking during sleep, but there is no reason for this.
As we have mentioned before, it can be due to very high fiber, stressful situations or overexertion.
In any case, this is a little-explored phenomenon.
The frequency with which it occurs is very variable.
It can be that one speaks calmly in individual words, whispers, or it can be quite the opposite (screaming, crying, long discussions).
In cases where the utterance is very intense, it is recommended to observe the child and to consult a specialist to check if there is a problem that causes anxiety and comes about in this way.
We have said that it is a positive disorder, so it will not be treated unless it is associated with some other sleep disorder that can be treated (for example, sleep apnea or stress).
What you can do is perform a series of simple preventive measures:
Try not to arouse the child before sleeping.
So, choose quiet play for the child and avoid stressful TV programmes that are awful and a bit too wild.
For the nervous children to whom relaxation is recommended, relaxation methods can be used to help them to get a certain inner peace.
This helps the child to sleep soundly.
Once speaking occurs during sleep, try to keep calm.
Remember that it is harmless to the child and the next day he will not be able to remember anything that happened.
Useful advice
Don't wake it up.
This is useless, for the child is unconscious, so you will pull him out of his sleep.
Although the child speaks, he sleeps, so he rests.
Remember, if the child is frightened after a couple of apparitions, it is recommended to seek counseling or to find out why the child is frightened.
When they understand what they are saying (which is not so common), the child does not put pressure on them to conduct an interrogation and get more information.
So you will not be able to achieve anything with it, because when the child sleeps, it is unconscious and cannot think about it.
Besides, you will hear what it says, but you will not know what it dreams and why it says it, so be careful with the interpretation of the information and the conclusions you draw from it.
