According to the Central Statistical Office, domestic sales prices rose by 0.1 percent in August 2008 compared to the previous month, and by 12.9 percent compared with August 2007.
Export prices were 1.1 percent higher than in July 2008, and down 3.9 percent from a year earlier.
Due to price changes in the domestic and export sectors, production prices were 0.7% higher than in the previous month, and 3.2% higher than in 2007.
Domestic sales prices rose only slightly, i.e. by 0.1 percent, compared to the previous month.
